        <div n="506-65L2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">By the same</hi>.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HE greatest monarch may be stabb'd by night,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-2"> And fortune help the murderer in his flight;<gap/><gap/></l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-3"> And calumny, by working under ground,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-4"> Can, unreveng'd, the greatest merit wound.What's to be done? Shall wit and learning chuse</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-5"> To live obscure, and have no fame to lose?</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-6"> By censure frighted, quit fair honour's road,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-7"> Nor dare to use the gifts by Heav'n bestow'd;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-8"> Or fearless enter in──thro' virtue's gate,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-506-65L2-line-9"> And buy <hi rend="underline">distinction</hi>, at the dearest rate.506-65L2   </l></lg></div>
